But the mask itself has `position: static` and no dimensions, so even though the `::after` pseudo-element has `position: absolute; inset: 0px`, the `::after` element can only position itself relative to the nearest positioned ancestor, which is NOT the `mint-cell-mask` (since it's `position: static`).

